@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - aispeech/TranscriptionJob
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateTranscriptionJob
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nSUCCEEDED
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in ACCEPTED,\nIN_PROGRESS, CANCELING,\nCANCELED
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in SUCCEEDED
observe --> retryable : OCI state in ACCEPTED,\nIN_PROGRESS, CANCELING,\nCANCELED
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\ndefined_tags, description,\ndisplay_name (+1 more)
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: aispeech
slug: transcriptionjob
kind: TranscriptionJob
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create ACCEPTED, IN_PROGRESS;
update ACCEPTED, IN_PROGRESS; delete CANCELING,
CANCELED
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
update=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: defined_tags, description,
display_name, freeform_tags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id
create-only fields:
model_details.transcription_settings.additional_settings
list lookup: oci_ai_speech_transcription_jobs
filters compartment_id, display_name, id; Exact
displayName or tracked OCID match within the
requested compartment.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
TranscriptionJob keeps the generated controller
and service-manager shell, but the handwritten
runtime client overrides lifecycle handling for
FAILED, CANCELING, and CANCELED while still
using generatedruntime request projection plus
read-after-write follow-up.
ACCEPTED and IN_PROGRESS remain the provisioning
states for both create and update. SUCCEEDED is
the only steady success state, FAILED is
terminal, and CANCELING is a terminating
breadcrumb during normal observe.
Delete confirmation is explicit repo-authored
behavior: CANCELING and CANCELED are
intermediate delete breadcrumbs only, and the
finalizer is retained until GetTranscriptionJob
confirms the resource is absent rather than
stopping at CANCELED.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place. compartmentId is
replacement-only, the refreshed
modelDetails.transcriptionSettings.additionalSettings
map is accepted on create and projected back
through status reads but remains create-only
drift because UpdateTranscriptionJobDetails
omits it, there are no secret side effects, and
the auxiliary CancelTranscriptionJob API remains
outside the published controller surface.
The pinned terraform-provider-oci revision has
no matching speech resource, so the import
catalog for this row is SDK-shaped and
repo-curated; the runtime semantics in this file
are the authoritative formal input for diagrams
and generator binding.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetTranscriptionJob or
ListTranscriptionJobs
delete targets: NOT_FOUND
end note
@enduml
